    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "runtests.py:\r\nWe should not use compiler flags for compiler defines. The different compilers have different command line syntaxes. There is a special parameter for this - compiler definitions (distutils.Extension(..., define_macros=...). \r\n\r\n**To Reproduce**\r\nexecute runtests.py on OpenVMS\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\nall tests must be done without errors\r\n\r\n**Environment (please complete the following information):**\r\n - OS: OpenVMS\r\n - Python version 3.8.2\r\n - Cython version 0.29.22\r\n",
    "closed_at": "2021-04-14T06:17:42Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
            "body": "It looks like we've tried to do this right at least once:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/cython/cython/blob/217a93e7b139ab49815ea9ca34142b3e2a116a08/runtests.py#L1143\r\n\r\nso it's probably a useful change to apply it to the other defines in runtest.py if possible.\r\n\r\nI don't know how easy it is to eliminate _all_ custom compiler arguments from runtests.py though",
            "created_at": "2021-04-06T17:14:11Z",
